unit.name: 2 Armored Division HQ
unit.History: The “Hell on Wheels” division had served in North Africa and Sicily before arriving in Normandy on June 2, 1944. It fought in France, Belgium, the Netherlands and Germany before it was send to the Ardennes to stem the German advance. The division was one of only two armored divisions (the other being the 3rd) which retained the old ‘square’ organization, with two armored regiments and one armored infantry regiment, making it a very powerful formation.

commander.Name: Ernest N. Harmon
commander.PersBio: Born in 1894, Ernest N. Harmon graduated from West Point in 1917 and served in the cavalry. From April 1943he commanded the 1st Armored Division in Tunisia and Italy, before being send back to the US as a corps commander after the fall of Rome. He returned to Europe to take over command of the 2nd Armored Division in September 1944. Among his troops, Harmon was known as "Old Gravel Voice".
